## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Security Middleware

#### [NEW] [rateLimiter.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/middleware/rateLimiter.js)
- IP-based rate limiter using `express-rate-limit`
- Defaults: **100 req/min** general, **20 req/min** for heavy routes (`/api/generate-token`)
- Configurable via `RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS` and `RATE_LIMIT_MAX` env vars
- Returns `429 Too Many Requests` with `Retry-After`, `X-RateLimit-Remaining`, `X-RateLimit-Reset` headers

#### [NEW] [auth.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/middleware/auth.js)
- JWT verification middleware — extracts `Bearer` token from `Authorization` header
- Attaches `req.user = { walletAddress }` to request on success
- Returns `401 Unauthorized` if token is missing/invalid/expired
- JWT tokens expire after 24 hours

---

### Backend — Authentication Routes

#### [NEW] [User.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/models/User.js)
- Mongoose model with fields: `walletAddress` (unique, lowercase), `nonce` (random string for signature verification), `createdAt`

#### [NEW] [authRoutes.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/routes/authRoutes.js)
Three endpoints for the MetaMask sign-in flow:
1. `GET /api/auth/nonce/:walletAddress` — Returns a random nonce for the user to sign (creates user record if first time)
2. `POST /api/auth/verify` — Accepts `{ walletAddress, signature }`, recovers the signer using `ethers.js`, issues a JWT if the signature is valid, rotates the nonce
3. `GET /api/auth/me` — Returns current user info from JWT (protected)

---

### Backend — Gas Estimator

#### [NEW] [gasRoutes.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/routes/gasRoutes.js)
- `POST /api/estimate-gas` — Takes `{ abi, bytecode, ownerAddress, supply }`, uses `ethers.JsonRpcProvider` with a public Sepolia RPC to estimate deployment gas, fetches current gas price, returns `{ gasUnits, gasPriceGwei, estimatedCostETH }`

---

### Backend — Security Audit Scanner

#### [NEW] [auditRoutes.js](file:///d:/Autocon-fyp/server/routes/auditRoutes.js)
- `POST /api/audit-contract` — Takes `{ contractCode }`, runs a pattern-based static analysis checking for:
  - Reentrancy patterns (`call.value`, state changes after external calls)
  - Unchecked return values
  - Use of `tx.origin` for authorization
  - Floating pragma versions  
  - Missing access control on sensitive functions
  - Unsafe math (pre-0.8.0 patterns)
- Returns `{ score, findings: [{ severity, title, description, line }] }`

